<inglise> Council Directive 76/580/EEC of 29 June 1976 amending Directive 73/239/EEC on the coordination of laws, regulations and administrative provisions relating to the taking up and pursuit of the business of direct insurance other than life assurance </inglise>
<eesti> n&otilde;ukogu direktiiv 76/580/EM&Uuml;, millega muudetakse direktiivi 73/239/EM&Uuml; otsekindlustustegevuse, v&auml;lja arvatud elukindlustustegevuse alustamise ja j&auml;tkamisega seotud &otilde;igusnormide koosk&otilde;lastamise kohta 29. juuni 1976 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular Article 57 (2) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artikli 57 l&otilde;iget 2, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Council Directive 73/239/EEC of 24 July 1973 on the co-ordination of laws, regulations and administrative provisions relating to the taking up and pursuit of the business of direct insurance other than life assurance (3), to facilitate the taking up and pursuit of the said business, has eliminated certain divergencies between national legislations; whereas it has ensured adequate protection for insured and third parties in all the Member States and, at the same time, co-ordinated in particular the provisions relating to the financial guarantees required of insurance undertakings; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: 24. juuli 1973. aasta esimene n&otilde;ukogu direktiiv 73/239/EM&Uuml; otsekindlustustegevuse, v&auml;lja arvatud elukindlustustegevuse alustamise ja j&auml;tkamisega seotud &otilde;igusnormide koosk&otilde;lastamise kohta (3) on nimetatud tegevuse alustamise ja j&auml;tkamise h&otilde;lbustamiseks k&otilde;rvaldanud teatavad lahknevused siseriiklike &otilde;igusaktide vahel; see on taganud k&otilde;igis liikmesriikides kindlustatud isikutele ja kolmandatele isikutele piisava kaitse ning koosk&otilde;lastanud samal ajal eesk&auml;tt kindlustusseltsidelt n&otilde;utavaid finantsgarantiisid k&auml;sitlevaid s&auml;tteid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, pursuant to that Directive, the minimum guarantee fund which each Member State requires of all insurance undertakings with head offices in its territory may not be less than certain amounts which are expressed in units of account in the Directive; </inglise>
<eesti> vastavalt sellele direktiivile ei tohi minimaalne garantiifond, mida iga liikmesriik n&otilde;uab oma territooriumil asuvate peakontoritega kindlustusseltsidelt, olla v&auml;iksem teatavatest selles direktiivis etten&auml;htud, arvestus&uuml;hikutes v&auml;ljendatud summadest; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the unit of account is also referred to in order to determine the amount of the contribution revenue of certain mutual associations below which the Directive does not apply; </inglise>
<eesti> samuti nimetatakse arvestus&uuml;hikut teatavate vastastikuste kindlustusseltside sissemaksetulu summa m&auml;&auml;ratlemisel, millest v&auml;iksema summa korral direktiivi ei kohaldata; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, for the purposes of the said Directive "unit of account" means that unit which is defined in Article 4 of the Protocol on the Statute of the European Investment Bank; whereas on the basis of this definition the conversion of the amounts mentioned in the Directive into national currencies would lead to distortions of competition between undertakings whose head offices are situated in the various Member States; </inglise>
<eesti> nimetatud direktiivis t&auml;hendab m&otilde;iste "arvestus&uuml;hik" protokolli Euroopa Investeerimispanga p&otilde;hikirja kohta artiklis 4 m&auml;&auml;ratletud &uuml;hikut; selle m&auml;&auml;ratluse alusel tooks direktiivis nimetatud summade konverteerimine riikide v&auml;&auml;ringusse kaasa konkurentsi moonutamise kindlustusseltside vahel, kelle peakontorid asuvad eri liikmesriikides; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas by Decision 75/250/EEC (4) the Council defined on 21 April 1975 a European unit of account representing the average of any changes in the value of the currencies of the Member States; whereas the conversion rate for each currency against this unit of account is fixed automatically by reference to daily quotations on the exchange markets; whereas the use of this European unit of account places insurance undertakings on the same competitive footing; </inglise>
<eesti> otsuses 75/250/EM&Uuml; (4) m&auml;&auml;ratles n&otilde;ukogu 21. aprillil 1975. aastal Euroopa arvestus&uuml;hiku, mis v&auml;ljendab liikmesriikide v&auml;&auml;ringute v&auml;&auml;rtuse k&otilde;igi muutuste keskmist; iga v&auml;&auml;ringu konverteerimiskurss selle arvestus&uuml;hiku suhtes m&auml;&auml;ratakse automaatselt valuutaturgude igap&auml;evaste noteeringute alusel; Euroopa arvestus&uuml;hiku kasutamine seab kindlustusseltsid konkurentsis v&otilde;rdsesse olukorda; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 4 of the aforesaid Protocol is undergoing revision; whereas, pursuant to the Decision of 18 March 1975 of the Board of Governors of the EIB, the Bank uses the European unit of account defined by Council Decision 75/250/EEC; </inglise>
<eesti> nimetatud protokolli artikkel 4 on l&auml;bivaatamisel; vastavalt EIP juhatajate n&otilde;ukogu 18. m&auml;rtsi 1975. aasta otsusele kasutab pank n&otilde;ukogu otsuses 75/250/EM&Uuml; m&auml;&auml;ratletud Euroopa arvestus&uuml;hikut; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas more recently, on 18 December 1975, the Commission, by Decision No 3289/75/ECSC (1), adopted, with the unanimous assent of the Council, this European unit of account in applying the Treaty establishing the European Coal and Steel Community; </inglise>
<eesti> komisjon v&otilde;ttis 18. detsembri 1975. aasta otsusega nr 3289/75/EST&Uuml; (5) n&otilde;ukogu &uuml;heh&auml;&auml;lsel n&otilde;usolekul selle Euroopa arvestus&uuml;hiku vastu Euroopa S&ouml;e- ja Terase&uuml;henduse asutamislepingu kohaldamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the value of the European unit of account in each of the Member States' currencies is fixed daily and whereas a reference day must also be fixed for its use when applying this Directive; </inglise>
<eesti> Euroopa arvestus&uuml;hiku v&auml;&auml;rtus iga liikmesriigi v&auml;&auml;ringus kinnitatakse iga p&auml;ev, samuti tuleb k&auml;esoleva direktiivi kohaldamisel kinnitada selle kasutamiseks v&otilde;rdlusp&auml;ev; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, however, in certain Member States the introduction of the European unit of account would lead to a reduction in terms of national currency of the amounts expressed in units of account in the Directive; whereas such a reduction would lead to a corresponding reduction in the protection now given to insured parties by the minimum guarantee fund; whereas the said amounts should be reviewed every two years; whereas, as a result of this review, the amounts in question are likely to be amended; whereas in certain Member States the reduction in the amounts expressed in national currency could, under these conditions, be swiftly followed by a further adjustment in those States; whereas the implementation of these successive measures would raise difficulties for undertakings and supervisory authorities; whereas, therefore, these amounts should be kept at the level which they would have reached on the basis of the conversion rate applicable before the introduction of the European unit of account, if this level is higher than that of the European unit of account, until the amounts fixed in Directive 73/239/EEC are reviewed; </inglise>
<eesti> teatavates liikmesriikides tooks Euroopa arvestus&uuml;hiku kasutuselev&otilde;tmine kaasa direktiivis arvestus&uuml;hikutena v&auml;ljendatud summade v&auml;henemise omav&auml;&auml;ringus; selline v&auml;henemine p&otilde;hjustaks praegu kindlustatud isikute jaoks minimaalse garantiifondiga antava kaitse vastavat v&auml;henemist; nimetatud summad tuleks iga kahe aasta j&auml;rel l&auml;bi vaadata; l&auml;bivaatamise tulemusena k&otilde;nealuseid summasid usutavasti muudetakse; teatavates liikmesriikides v&otilde;ib omav&auml;&auml;ringus v&auml;ljendatud summade v&auml;henemisele neis tingimustes kiiresti j&auml;rgneda edasine korrigeerimine; nende j&auml;rjestikuste meetmete rakendamine tekitaks kindlustusseltsidele ja j&auml;relevalveasutustele raskusi; kuni direktiivis 73/239/EM&Uuml; kinnitatud summade l&auml;bivaatamiseni tuleks need summad seet&otilde;ttu hoida tasemel, millele nad oleksid j&otilde;udnud konverteerimiskursi alusel, mida kohaldati enne Euroopa arvestus&uuml;hiku kehtestamist, juhul kui see tase on k&otilde;rgem Euroopa arvestus&uuml;hiku tasemest; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas changes in the economic and monetary situation of the Community justify the examination at regular intervals of the latter amounts, </inglise>
<eesti> &uuml;henduse majandusliku ja rahalise olukorra muutused &otilde;igustavad viimaste summade korrap&auml;rast l&auml;bivaatamist, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DIRECTIVE: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA DIREKTIIVI. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The following shall be substituted for the text of Article 5 (a) of Directive 73/239/EEC: </inglise>
<eesti> Direktiivi 73/239/EM&Uuml; artikli 5 punkt a asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> "(a) Unit of account means the European unit of account (EUA) as defined by Commission Decision 3289/75/ECSC (1). </inglise>
<eesti> "a) arvestus&uuml;hik - komisjoni otsusega 3289/75/EST&Uuml; (1) m&auml;&auml;ratletud Euroopa arvestus&uuml;hik (EA&Uuml;). </eesti>
<inglise> Wherever this Directive refers to the unit of account, the conversion value in national currency to be adopted shall, as from 31 December of each year, be that of the last day of the preceding month of October for which EUA conversion values are available in all the Community currencies;". </inglise>
<eesti> Kui k&auml;esolevas direktiivis nimetatakse arvestus&uuml;hikut, v&otilde;etakse konverteerimisv&auml;&auml;rtuseks omav&auml;&auml;ringus alates iga aasta 31. detsembrist v&auml;&auml;rtus eelmise oktoobrikuu viimasel p&auml;eval, mille kohta EA&Uuml; konverteerimisv&auml;&auml;rtused on k&otilde;igis &uuml;henduse v&auml;&auml;ringutes k&auml;ttesaadavad;". </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The following note is added as a footnote to the page where Article 5 of Directive 73/239/EEC appears: </inglise>
<eesti> Lehek&uuml;ljele, kus on direktiivi 73/239/EM&Uuml; artikkel 5, lisatakse j&auml;rgmine joonealune m&auml;rkus: </eesti>
<inglise> "(1) OJ No L 327, 19.12.1975, p. 4.". </inglise>
<eesti> "(1) E&Uuml;T L 327, 19.12.1975, lk 4." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> As an transitional measure and until the amounts expressed in units of account in Directive 73/239/EEC have been amended for the first time, the amounts expressed in national currency for conversion of the unit of account, as defined in Article 5 (a), shall not be less than those derived according to the rate of conversion applicable to the unit of account before the adoption of this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;leminekumeetmena ja kuni direktiivis 73/239/EM&Uuml; arvestus&uuml;hikutena v&auml;ljendatud summade esmakordse muutmiseni ei tohi artikli 5 punktis a m&auml;&auml;ratletud arvestus&uuml;hiku konverteerimiseks m&otilde;eldud omav&auml;&auml;ringus v&auml;ljendatud summad olla v&auml;iksemad kui summad, mis tuletatakse vastavalt enne k&auml;esoleva direktiivi vastuv&otilde;tmist arvestus&uuml;hiku suhtes kohaldatavale konverteerimiskursile. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> Every two years, the Council, acting on a proposal from the Commission, shall review and if necessary amend the amounts expressed in Directive 73/239/EEC in units of account, taking into account changes in the economic and monetary situation of the Community. </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;ukogu vaatab komisjoni ettepaneku p&otilde;hjal iga kahe aasta j&auml;rel &uuml;le ja vajaduse korral muudab direktiivis 73/239/EM&Uuml; arvestus&uuml;hikutes v&auml;ljendatud summasid, v&otilde;ttes arvesse &uuml;henduse majandusliku ja rahalise olukorra muutusi. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> The national provisions amended in accordance with this Directive shall be applicable as from 31 December 1976. </inglise>
<eesti> Vastavalt k&auml;esolevale direktiivile muudetud siseriiklikke &otilde;igusnorme kohaldatakse alates 31. detsembrist 1976. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> This Directive is addressed to the Member States. Done at Luxembourg, 29 June 1976. </inglise>
